The RDP port of your windows machine can be changed through the following steps:

 

Take the run option from your windows startup menu.

**Type  regedit and click run**.

**Find the  RDP-Tcp key under the  HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE**

Next look for the  subkey named PortNumber. The port number values are shown in their hexadecimal values. Convert this to the decimal system. 

Next change the  port number and save.

 Next reboot your  server and you are all set.
